                           <collation>
                              
                              
                              
                              <p>Folios 16 to 235 form 22 complete quires of 10 leaves each, signed with hebrew letters on the last page and also marked by catchwords.</p>
                              
                              
                              
                              <p>Folios 7 to 15 are the remaining leaves of the second quire.</p>
                              
                              
                              
                              <p>Folios 1 to 6 have been added later (probably in 16th century) to supply the deficiency at the beginnig.</p>
                              
                              
                              
                              <p>Folding of folios 236 to 242 is uncertain.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           </collation>
                           
                           
                           
                           <condition>
                              
                              
                              
                              <p>Several lacunas.</p>
                           
                           
                           
